member.example:
This sample shows how to call CreateProjectAsync with required parameters.

var endpoint = new Uri("<https://my-service.azure.com>");
var client = new LroBasicCadlClient(endpoint);

var data = new {};

var operation = await client.CreateProjectAsync(WaitUntil.Started, RequestContent.Create(data));

var response = await operation.WaitForCompletionResponseAsync();
Console.WriteLine(response.Status)

This sample shows how to call CreateProjectAsync with all parameters and request content.

var endpoint = new Uri("<https://my-service.azure.com>");
var client = new LroBasicCadlClient(endpoint);

var data = new {
    description = "<description>",
    name = "<name>",
};

var operation = await client.CreateProjectAsync(WaitUntil.Started, RequestContent.Create(data));

var response = await operation.WaitForCompletionResponseAsync();
Console.WriteLine(response.Status)

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the request payload.
Request Body:
Schema for Project: { id: string, # Required. description: string, # Optional. name: string, # Optional. }

